{
  "id": "5",
  "title": "5. Subagents, Tools & Lifecycle Hooks",
  "type": "lab",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "# [5. Subagents, Tools & Lifecycle Hooks]"
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "content": "Autonomy Control, Custom Tools & Hooks"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "To build reliable, secure pipelines, developers must inspect agent actions and register custom tooling capabilities. This module details enabling subagents, registering local code tools, and intercepting executions with hooks."
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Defining Custom Tools & Subagent Spawning"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Registering custom Python functions or Node.js functions as tools allows agents to fetch data, compute hashes, or query databases. Spawning subagents is configured in the CapabilitiesConfig object (enabled by default)."
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Human-in-the-Loop Gateways"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Using the pre_tool_call_decide hook, you can pause agent execution immediately before a tool is run. This allows you to check arguments, log execution traces, or prompt a human operator for explicit permission."
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Python Integration Pipeline"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "This script registers a custom hashing tool, enables subagents, and configures a session start hook and tool approval gate."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "import asyncio",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "from google.antigravity import Agent, LocalAgentConfig, types",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "from google.antigravity.hooks import hooks",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# 1. Define custom function tool",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "def calculate_hash(data: str) -> str:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "\"\"\"Calculates the SHA-256 hash of a string.\"\"\"",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "import hashlib",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "return hashlib.sha256(data.encode()).hexdigest()",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# 2. Define lifecycle hook functions",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "@hooks.on_session_start",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "async def on_session_start_handler():",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "print('[HOOK] Session started')",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "@hooks.pre_tool_call_decide",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "async def on_pre_tool_handler(tool_call: types.ToolCall) -> types.HookResult:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "print(f'[GATE] Requested Tool: {tool_call.name}')",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "print(f'[GATE] Tool arguments: {tool_call.args}')",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# Simulate user approval prompt",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "confirm = input('Approve this execution? (yes/no): ').strip().lower()",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "if confirm == 'yes':",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "return types.HookResult(allow=True)",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "print('[GATE] Execution denied.')",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "return types.HookResult(allow=False)",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "async def main():",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# Register tools, capabilities, and hooks",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "config = LocalAgentConfig(",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "tools=[calculate_hash],",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "capabilities=types.CapabilitiesConfig(",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "enable_subagents=True",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "),",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "hooks=[on_session_start_handler, on_pre_tool_handler]",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": ")",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "async with Agent(config) as agent:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "response = await agent.chat(\"Generate the hash for 'Antigravity'.\")",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "print(await response.text())",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "if __name__ == '__main__':",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "asyncio.run(main())",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Node.js Integration Pipeline"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Below is the equivalent implementation in Node.js, detailing tool registration parameters and registering lifecycle handlers."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "import { Agent, LocalAgentConfig } from '@google/antigravity';",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "import readline from 'readline';",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "// 1. Define custom hashing function",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "function calculateHash(args) {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const { data } = args;",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "import crypto from 'crypto';",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(data).digest('hex');",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "// Helper to read console input",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "function askUser(query) {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const rl = readline.createInterface({",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "input: process.stdin,",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "output: process.stdout",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "});",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "return new Promise(resolve => rl.question(query, ans => {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "rl.close();",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "resolve(ans);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}));",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "async function main() {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const config = new LocalAgentConfig({",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "tools: [",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "{",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "name: 'calculateHash',",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "description: 'Calculates the SHA-256 hash of a string.',",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "parameters: {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "type: 'object',",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "properties: {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "data: { type: 'string' }",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "},",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "required: ['data']",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "},",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "execute: calculateHash",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "],",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "capabilities: {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "enableSubagents: true",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "},",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "hooks: {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "onSessionStart: async () => {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "console.log('[HOOK] Session started');",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "},",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "preToolCallDecide: async (toolCall) => {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "console.log(`[GATE] Requested Tool: ${toolCall.name}`);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "console.log(`[GATE] Tool arguments:`, toolCall.args);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const ans = await askUser('Approve this execution? (yes/no): ');",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "if (ans.trim().toLowerCase() === 'yes') {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "return { allow: true };",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "console.log('[GATE] Execution denied.');",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "return { allow: false };",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "});",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const agent = new Agent(config);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "await agent.start();",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "try {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const response = await agent.chat('Generate the hash for \"Antigravity\".');",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "console.log(await response.text());",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "} finally {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "await agent.stop();",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "main().catch(console.error);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Check Your Understanding"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Question 1: Which hook is used to intercept and block tool executions?"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- A) pre_turn"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- B) pre_tool_call_decide"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- C) post_tool_call"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- D) on_session_end"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Feedback: Correct Answer: B. The pre_tool_call_decide hook intercepts the tool call after scheduling but prior to execution, allowing for approval decisions."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Question 2: How do you enable subagent spawning in LocalAgentConfig?"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- A) Pass enable_subagents=True directly to the main config constructor."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- B) Set capabilities=types.CapabilitiesConfig(enable_subagents=True) in the configuration variables."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- C) Load a specific Model Context Protocol server."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- D) Register a subagent spawn hook in the hooks array."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Feedback: Correct Answer: B. Subagents are enabled inside the capabilities object within the main LocalAgentConfig initialization."
    }
  ]
}